{
  "texts": [
    "Fair use of data means ensuring that it is fit for purpose and respect the principle of human autonomy by developing AI systems that support consumers in their decision-making process.",
    "Insurance firms should make reasonable efforts to monitor and mitigate biases from data and AI systems.",
    "This may include using more explainable algorithms or developing fairness and non-discrimination metrics in high-impact AI applications.",
    "Insurance firms should develop their approach to fairness and keep records on the measures put in place to ensure fairness and non-discrimination\"",
    "Equality Act Under the Equality Act of 2010, unfair treatment (including direct and indirect discrimination, harassment, and victimisation) on the basis of certain protected characteristics is not permitted."
  ]
}